				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Opinons on OoW<a name="56561"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 13 04 11:39 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It's called progression, or mudflation, as some would call it. I think it's somewhat of a necessary thing, but I'm a high-end raider so my opinion is probably different from a lot of the more casual gamers. A lot of guilds finished PoP and were forced to sit around and farm PoTime for months because they didn't have anything better to do since there was no more content to progress through. Finally GoD comes out and everyone is merrily making their way through it again. Soon GoD will be conquered and everyone will move on to OoW. The items will get better, the mobs will get harder, it's just a natural progression. The older content will become more and more trivial, but the way I see it, that's going to happen when you have a game that's been running for this long.
<br />

<br />
Also, the increase in player power derived from easier availablity of more powerful items gives lower guilds that previously would not be able to do some content the ability to do so, so it's not like the progression is only for the uberguilds. 
<br />

<br />
Like I said, this is from a high end point of view. But I would think a lot of the casual gamers could relate to some degree, too. Grinding in DL, or PoN, or LDoN gets boring after you've done it ten billion times. You want new content to see and experience, do you not? The game-wide progression of stronger items/skills/levels will help you do that newer content.
<br />

<br />
I personally am enjoying EQ at the moment, and am looking forward to new experiences in OoW. I think I enjoy it more becuase of my guild than the acutal game, but I have to say I've had less complaints now than I've probably ever had in my 3 1/2 years of EQ. I've always loved raiding and I really do like some of the encounters in GoD. Does it bother me that older content is made trivial? Not really, they were fun and challenging in their own time. Without a progression, I think EQ would stagnate and die rather quickly. I don't really expect everyone to agree with me, but that's just my 2cp<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
