				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm not going to buy eq2, WoW, nor any other MMORPG.  One MMORPG is enough for me, and, SOMETIMES, that's too much!   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
As far as eq goes (and it's expansions), several weeks ago I had NO intention whatsoever of buying ANY more expansions.  I, like so many other people, was frustrated with the accumulation of older &quot;broken&quot; content that wasn't getting fixed, as well as SOE's apparent lack of caring for customer concerns.  Then &quot;The Summit&quot; happened.  Out of that, came class representatives, Top 10 Class Issues (that SOE has promised to keep giving status updates on), etc.  I choose (for the time being) to give SOE the benefit of the doubt that they are finally listening to our concerns and are doing something about those concerns.  Heck, fixing off-hand double-attack was a smaller concern on our list, but it's fixed now.  *Cheer*  I suppose I'll go ahead and buy the new OOW expansion because I choose to believe (at this point) that SOE is starting to REALLY try to please us (player base).
<br />

<br />
You can bet that I won't purchase any more expansions, though, if they (SOE) drop the ball on &quot;player relations&quot; again.  Time will certainly tell.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
