				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't want to go too far here and I don't want this to come across as a flame but here goes....
<br />
   People are way too caught up in this stuff. 90% of the problems in EQ between class wars and rude encouters come from ignorance and the fact that most people feel comfortable making themselves part of a group and feel the need to stubbornly defend said group, otherwise it's like admitting they were wrong. I mean this class to class, but I also mean it with EQ itself. It's a cycle and if you tell yourself anything else you're not fooling anyone. I won't say anything as stupid as &quot;It's a god d*mn video game get over it!&quot; because it's obviously not that simple or there wouldn't be message boards like this. You don't need to justify anything, if you want to spend $40.00 on a game, then dammit do it because you want to. If you don't like where the game is going, then you've got to do something about it for YOURSELF. Make a new toon, pick a new server, try PvP, or take a break for once. People act so helpless, like there's these big wigs up there at SoE calling all the shots and there's nothing they can do about it, consumer power is Amazing in itself but freedom of choice is at the root of it all. Do something for yourself, it's the only way. One day they're going to pull the plug, no matter how much it pisses people off, and all the decisions we try to justify, all the time spent is going to be history, a lot of people are going to realize we've been wrong all along. 
<br />
  Now, I realize there's more to it than that. This is a community, I think the sense of community has a lot to do with what makes people play EQ for so long, but within the community are individuals. I stopped playing every day about 2 months ago and my entire view of the game has changed. I talk to my old EQ friends through AIM, e-mail and even on the phone, but I barely play once a week now. The concerns for balance are gone, the gameplay is fresh and I am, in general, much more happy with things in game and out. Yeh I won't see plane of time, upper GoD or the upper OoW but I will absolutely still see people bickering and wasting all sorts of time being totally pissed off about something they honestly have complete control over and don't even realize it. 
<br />
   Don't limit yourself is all I'm trying to say. If you want to care about something, care about the people in the game who make you feel good and make you glad to play, they're the ones who deserve attention, not some yuppie sitting behind his desk calling all the shots on new content. Screw that guy, screw OoW, screw WoW and screw Vanguard, the people are what matter and if everyone's going to get caught up in taking sides on something like this, individuals will continue to get overlooked and  lose what makes this game so much fun, individuality itself. 
<br />
   Think about the best times you've had in EQ, they've never been because of the content, they've always been because of the people you meet and bond with, that's how I see it anyways. The only reason I even sign on anymore is because of the folks I've met and I'm always really happy to see them, whether I'm in GoD, Kunark, Velious or what have you, it doesn't matter one bit. I see a bunch of money hungry morons with absolutely no clue what people really want, running this game. Sometimes they hit it, sometimes they miss it, but either way we keep playing, which proves my point because if the content was really that important, most of us would have quit by now. Screw it man, I'm all over the place and I don't know where I'm really going with this but I hope I made at least one or two decent points. Just try and be careful what you put your energy into, sometimes something seems so obvious, but well all know hindsight is never 20/20. 
<br />

<br />
And I'm spent.
<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" /></span></td>
