				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Opinons on OoW<a name="56607"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 13 04 3:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think it is funny when someone complains about expansions making older content trivial.  Every single expansion has done this.  Kunark made Original EQ trivial, Velious did it to Kunark, etc.  The only two expansions that really did not have this effect were LDoN and LoY.  Both of these were aimed at casual players, and as such, did not raise the bar.
<br />

<br />
I will say that I really like GoD.  There are plenty of things that do irritate me (54 person raid limit, some of the itemization), but it brought back the difficulty to the game.  I started EQ at the release of Kunark, and the game was &quot;hard&quot; then.  Dying was easy, and rezzes were difficult to get.  Fear was a full raid, and a wipe meant getting help from other guilds.  You could fall into the Hole in Paineel, and hae to petition for your corpse.  
<br />

<br />
Over time, the game was made easier and easier.  Graveyards, PoK books, much lower mob densities, a lot of outdoor zones.  Invisible rails on bridges and chasms in LDoN compared to the gorge in the Deep is a good example.  I guess Sony figured that the game would appeal to more people if the element of danger was removed.  Instead, it made the game boring in my opinion.
<br />

<br />
Back to the GoD/OoW discussion.  Gone are the graveyards, 1 hop from PoK, invisible rails, and low mob densities.  eope traveled in groups from Natimbi to Barindu for safety.  You brought an alt rezzer to prevent hideous CR's.  It brought the challenge back.  I believe it brought the fun back.  
<br />

<br />
Kanarian, Bard of Saryrn
<br />
Impressario of The War Council</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
