				<td colspan="2"><span>OoW is the last chance I'm giving SOE.  
<br />

<br />
GoD, LoY, and LDoN were all sad sad excuses for &quot;expansions&quot;.  Look at the amount of content VERANT (yes the good development team) gave with the first 2 expansions and then SOE got off to a good start with their first two.  You could go from lvl 1 to 60 in Kunark or Luclin.  Even though PoP was geared towards the high end game, they didn't SCREW over the non-ubers, by say.. making all new spells no drop.
<br />

<br />
But after PoP, everything went downhill and they released these small one disc expansions that were just an insult for the amount of money they costed.  LDoN was a cool idea.. but really got old fast.  The entire LoY expansion could have been a patch..
<br />

<br />
But GoD was the last straw.  A one disc expansion geared ENTIRELY towards the very upper end.  They still tricked everyone into buying it cuz of the new class.  This was not an expansion.  An expansion should take more than two months for the top guilds to defeat.  Take a clue from what Verant did with the first two and then the huge amount of content in Luclin and PoP and stop dishing out these rushed crappy rip-offs you call expansions.
<br />

<br />
what the h*ll happened to the original lore in Everquest that people cared about?  Veeshan, the Sleeper, Dragons and the factions of goblins and stuff that followed them?  I don't give a crap about some Wayfarer Brotherhood.
<br />

<br />
OoW looks like it might have some sort of decent lore to it.  I guess SOE is getting the clue that some people still care about that.  I'll give it a chance, but if its another crappy 1-disc lvl 65+ expansion, forget it.</span></td>
